gomodel:SYNGO_542  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1\nMAGI2 is localized at inhibitory synapses.\nLiteral\n\"We found that 32.1 ± 5.4% of S-SCAM clusters were apposed to VGAT clusters, whereas 69.8 ± 5.8% of VGAT clusters were apposed to S-SCAM clusters. We also immunostained cells with anti-gephyrin antibody (Fig. 1b, lower panel). We found that 35.4 ± 7.4% of S-SCAM clusters were co-localized with gephyrin clusters, whereas 62.7 ± 10.9% of gephyrin clusters were co-localized with S-SCAM clusters. These findings suggest that almost one-third of signals detected by anti-S-SCAM antibody arelocalized at inhibitory synapses.\"\nFig. 8e\nMAGI2 colocalized with neuroligin 2 at inhibitory synapses.\nLiteral\n\"In the immunofluorescence of rat primary cultured hippocampal neurons, neuroligin 2 was partially overlapped with S-SCAM and b-DG\"\n\n24/5/2017 Pim\n- Fig.1 shows that MAGI2 is localized at inh. synapses.\n- Fig.8a shows direct interaction of the cytosolic MAGI2 protein with transmembrane neurologin 2.\n- Fig.8e shows colocalization of MAGI2 and neuroligin 2 in inhibitory synapses.\nNeuroligin is a known postsynapic protein of inhibitory synapses that interacts with presynaptic neurexin proteins.\nIn conclusion, via PPI and colocalization with neuroligin 2 a postsynaptic localization of MAGI2 is evidenced. Since MAGI2 interacts with the TM neuroligin protein the membrane association type is \"extrinsic component....\". Experimental description: Experiment of immunohistochemistry are made in rat.\nLiteral from M&M\n\"Hippocampal neuron cultures were obtained from rat embryonic day-18 (E18) embryos as described previously (Goslin and Banker 1991)\".\n\nFig.8: \"Co-localization of S-SCAM, β-DG and neuroligin 2 at inhibitory synapses. Rat primary cultured hippocampal neurons were immunostained with rabbit anti-S-SCAM (14-64), ....\" (rat neurons, endogenous protein is investigated)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_542" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

